2 Subsections (4)(a) and (4)(b) do not apply for other purposes, including:
3 (a) treatment for a person born with a medically verifiable disorder of sex development, including:
4 (i) a person born with external biological sex characteristics that are irresolvably ambiguous,
5 including an individual born with 46 XX chromosomes with virilization, an individual born with 46 XY
6 chromosomes with undervirilization, or an individual having both ovarian and testicular tissue; and
7 (ii) a person whom a physician has otherwise diagnosed with a disorder of sexual development in
8 which the physician has determined through genetic or biochemical testing that the person does not have
9 normal sex chromosome structure, sex steroid hormone production, or sex steroid hormone action for a male or
10 female; and
11 (b) treatment of any infection, injury, disease, or disorder that has been caused or exacerbated by
12 a medical treatment listed in subsection (4)(a) or (4)(b), whether or not the medical treatment was performed in
13 accordance with state and federal law and whether or not funding for the medical treatment is permissible
14 under state and federal law.
15 (6) As used in this section, unless the context clearly indicates otherwise, the following definitions
16 apply:
17 (a) "Female" means a member of the human species who, under normal development, has XX
18 chromosomes and produces or would produce relatively large, relatively immobile gametes, or eggs, during her
19 life cycle and has a reproductive and endocrine system oriented around the production of those gametes. An
20 individual who would otherwise fall within this definition, but for a biological or genetic condition, is female for
21 the purposes of this section.
22 (b) "Gender" means the psychological, behavioral, social, and cultural aspects of being male or
23 female.
24 (c) "Health care professional" means a person who is licensed, certified, or otherwise authorized
25 by the laws of this state to administer health care in the ordinary course of the practice of the person's
26 profession.
27 (d) "Male" means a member of the human species who, under normal development, has XY
28 chromosomes and produces or would produce small, mobile gametes, or sperm, during his life cycle and has a
