12 SECTION 2. SECTION 27-2-205, MCA, IS AMENDED TO READ:
13 "27-2-205. Actions for medical malpractice. (1) Action in tort or contract for injury or death against a
14 physician or surgeon, physician assistant, dentist, dental hygienist, registered nurse, advanced practice
15 registered nurse, nursing home or hospital administrator, dispensing optician, optometrist, licensed physical
16 therapist, podiatrist, psychologist, osteopath, chiropractor, clinical laboratory bioanalyst, clinical laboratory
17 technologist, pharmacist, veterinarian, a licensed hospital or long-term care facility, or licensed medical
18 professional corporation, based upon alleged professional negligence or for rendering professional services
19 without consent or for an act, error, or omission, must, except as provided in subsection subsections (2) and
20 (3), be commenced within 2 years after the date of injury or within 2 years after the plaintiff discovers or through
21 the use of reasonable diligence should have discovered the injury, whichever occurs last, but in no case may
22 an action be commenced after 5 years from the date of injury. However, this time limitation is tolled for any
23 period during which there has been a failure to disclose any act, error, or omission upon which an action is
24 based and that is known to the defendant or through the use of reasonable diligence subsequent to the act,
25 error, or omission would have been known to the defendant.
26 (2) Notwithstanding the provisions of 27-2-401, in an action for death or injury of a minor who was
27 under the age of 4 on the date of the minor's injury, the period of limitations in subsection (1) begins to run
28 when the minor reaches the minor's eighth birthday or dies, whichever occurs first, and the time for
